    <text id="F0030T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Potter writes a general letter of inquiry to his son ("Josey").</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Son</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-03-06">March 6 1864 </date>
                        <name type="place">Hospital Department 16th Pa Cavalry </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Dear Son </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I was very much pleased to get a letter from you &amp; hope you will write
                    another soon. You wrote that Mother &amp; yourself Lucy Bell and Jimmie were
                    all well. </p>

                <p>Pa is very well &amp; would like to hear your speech. There is a little boy
                    about as big as you here he is on a horse every day riding around.</p>

                <p>Have you got your drum yet. If you study now like a good boy you will have a fine
                    chance to play on it when school is out. Josey be good to your Mother and your
                    brother and sisters &amp; then you will be good to yourself. God will love
                    you &amp; Pa &amp; Mother &amp; all of us will love you more than
                    ever. May God bless my little children &amp; keep them from all evil to
                    himself.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your affectionate Father </salute>
                    <signed>Samuel M. Potter </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
